 |oclc=5788147
}}</ref> the [[common cold]], [[clinical depression|depression]], [[drug addiction]], [[drug overdose]], [[epilepsy]], [[heart diseases]], [[heavy metal poisoning|heavy metal toxicity]], acute [[hepatitis]], [[herpes]], [[hyperactivity]], [[hypertension]], [[hypoglycemia]], [[influenza]], [[learning disabilities]], [[mental disorder|mental]] and [[metabolic disorders]],<ref>Princeton Brain Bio Center. Brochure, distributed to patients. Skillman, New Jersey, 1983, The Center.</ref> [[migraine]], [[Infectious mononucleosis|mononucleosis]], [[mushroom poisoning]], [[neuropathy]] & [[polyneuritis]] (including [[multiple sclerosis]]), [[osteoporosis]],<ref>
{{cite pmid|15771560}}</ref> [[polio]], an hypothesised condition called "pyroluria", [[radiation sickness]], [[Raynaud's disease]], [[mental retardation]], [[schizophrenia]],<ref name="SkinnerP">
